Adaptive Histogram Equalization in OpenCV¶

In [5]:
b,g,r = cv2.split(img1) # split channels

clahe = cv2.createCLAHE(clipLimit=2.0, tileGridSize=(8,8)) # create a CLAHE object (Arguments are optional).
b = cv2.equalizeHist(b)
g = cv2.equalizeHist(g)
r = cv2.equalizeHist(r)

img2 = cv2.merge((b, g, r))

plt.imshow(img2);plt.title('Result')

Threshold -> mask¶

In [29]:
gray_image = cv2.cvtColor(img1, cv2.COLOR_RGB2GRAY)
blur = cv2.GaussianBlur(gray_image,(5,5),0) # it returns a RGB image
ret, mask = cv2.threshold(blur, 0, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY+cv2.THRESH_OTSU)
plt.imshow(mask),plt.title('Mask')

In [82]:
r,g,b = cv2.split(res2) # split channels

KERNEL_SIZE = 21
clahe = cv2.createCLAHE(clipLimit=2.0, tileGridSize=(8,8)) # create a CLAHE object (Arguments are optional).
r = cv2.equalizeHist(cv2.GaussianBlur(r,(KERNEL_SIZE,KERNEL_SIZE),0))
g = cv2.equalizeHist(cv2.GaussianBlur(g,(KERNEL_SIZE,KERNEL_SIZE),0))
b = cv2.equalizeHist(cv2.GaussianBlur(b,(KERNEL_SIZE,KERNEL_SIZE),0))

enhanced_dark = cv2.merge((r, g, b))
enhanced_dark = cv2.fastNlMeansDenoisingColored(enhanced_dark,None,10,10,7,21)
plt.imshow(enhanced_dark);plt.title('Enhanced')
